Orders & Fulfillment Workflow – Locked Specification

Scope

This document fully locks item 4: Orders & Fulfillment workflow for the Java backend.

It defines:
	•	Order lifecycle (fulfillment)
	•	Payment lifecycle (aligned with previously locked payment decisions)
	•	Interaction rules between payment and fulfillment
	•	Merchant Admin operational capabilities
	•	Minimum data model requirements

Out of scope (intentionally deferred):
	•	Shipping rates engine
	•	Tax engine
	•	Inventory reservations
	•	Partial refunds / returns
	•	Advanced logistics integrations

⸻

1. Core Principles (Locked)

1.1 Separate lifecycles

Orders have two independent but related state machines:
	•	Payment status (money)
	•	Fulfillment status (operational execution)

This separation is mandatory to support offline payments and manual confirmation.

1.2 Offline-first design

The workflow must fully support:
	•	Cash
	•	Nequi
	•	Bank transfer

with merchant-controlled validation.

1.3 Tenant & permission safety
	•	All order actions are tenant-scoped
	•	Authorization enforced via centralized policy
	•	Only ADMIN and STAFF can manage orders
	•	STAFF is allowed to refund

⸻

2. Payment Workflow (Locked)

2.1 Supported payment methods (MVP)
	•	CASH
	•	NEQUI
	•	BANK_TRANSFER
	•	WOMPI (online PSP, merchant-owned accounts)

⸻

2.2 Payment status states (Locked)

Status	Meaning
UNPAID	Order created, no payment initiated
PENDING	Customer instructed to pay / payment attempt created
WAITING_CONFIRMATION	Optional review state (offline proof submitted)
PAID	Payment confirmed (merchant or PSP webhook)
FAILED	Online payment failed
REFUNDED	Full refund completed

Notes:
	•	Offline payments typically go PENDING → PAID
	•	Wompi transitions are webhook-driven and authoritative

⸻

3. Fulfillment Workflow (Locked)

3.1 Fulfillment type (per order)
	•	PICKUP
	•	DELIVERY
	•	DIGITAL (future)

⸻

3.2 Fulfillment status states (Locked)

Status	Meaning
NEW	Order placed by customer
CONFIRMED	Merchant explicitly accepted the order
FULFILLING	Order being prepared
READY	Ready for pickup or out for delivery
COMPLETED	Delivered or picked up
CANCELLED	Cancelled before completion

Locked decisions
	•	CONFIRMED step is required (merchant must confirm order)
	•	READY is used instead of OUT_FOR_DELIVERY

⸻

4. Interaction Rules: Payment vs Fulfillment (Locked)

4.1 Gating rules by payment method

Nequi / Bank Transfer
	•	Fulfillment cannot move to FULFILLING unless payment is PAID

Cash
Two supported behaviors (merchant setting):
	•	Cash on pickup/delivery (default)
	•	Fulfillment may proceed while payment is PENDING
	•	Payment becomes PAID when cash is received
	•	Cash requires prepayment
	•	Same gating as transfer payments

⸻

4.2 Cancellation rules
	•	If fulfillment_status == COMPLETED → cancellation not allowed
	•	If cancelled after payment → refund required

⸻

5. Merchant Admin Capabilities (Locked)

5.1 Order list

Filters:
	•	Date range
	•	Payment status
	•	Fulfillment status
	•	Payment method
	•	Fulfillment type

⸻

5.2 Order detail view

Displays:
	•	Order items (product snapshots)
	•	Totals
	•	Customer contact info
	•	Delivery details (if applicable)
	•	Payment method + status
	•	Payment proof (offline)
	•	Audit timeline

⸻

5.3 Allowed actions (ADMIN & STAFF)
	•	Confirm order (NEW → CONFIRMED)
	•	Update fulfillment status (CONFIRMED → FULFILLING → READY → COMPLETED)
	•	Mark payment as paid (offline)
	•	Upload/view payment proof
	•	Cancel order (with reason)
	•	Refund order (full refund only, MVP)

Permissions:
	•	Requires ORDER_MANAGE
	•	Refund requires REFUND_MANAGE

⸻

6. Refund Workflow (Locked)

6.1 Refund scope (MVP)
	•	Full refunds only
	•	No partial refunds

6.2 Refund handling
	•	Offline payments: merchant performs refund externally and records it
	•	Wompi: PSP refund API used later; system records result

Refund action sets:
	•	payment_status = REFUNDED
	•	Creates refund/audit event

